## 3. Docker Installation

1. Admin Rechte verlangen - sudo su 
2. Paketquellen aktualisieren: apt update
3. Basispakete installieren: apt install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gpg
4. Docker schlüssel: curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | \
gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg
5. Paketquelle hinzufügen: echo "deb [arch=amd64 \
signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] \
https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
$(lsb_release -cs) stable" > \
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list
6. apt update
7. apt install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
8. vmadmin zur Gruppe Docker hinzufügen - usermod -aG docker vmadmin 
9. Test ob funktionert: docker run hello-world




## 4. Image installation: docker build -t welcome-to-docker .

